cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper presents a new way of embedding functional languages into Coq, which is a programming language and proof assistant. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the meta-theory of the language and provides a soundness theorem connecting the deep and shallow embeddings, which involves logical reasoning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper develops an embedding of a smart contract language and verifies several important properties of a crowdfunding contract, which involves software engineering techniques. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper mentions a previous formalisation of smart contract execution in blockchains, which involves cryptography and security. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): Although not the main focus, the paper may involve some data structures and algorithms in the implementation of the embedding and verification of properties.
